## [1] "Regression analysis of test scores as a function of gender and urbanicity, and tutoring dose."
## [1] "You might think this makes things better because dose is an important confounder. But controlling for it creates other issues. We don't know how people self-select into tutoring. So the other coefficients could still be biased. For example, the highly motivated men may be the ones with high takeup. This can upward-bias the dosage coefficient and downward-bias the male coefficient."
##
